    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="520">
      <subfield code="a">We theoretically analyze the ground state of weakly interacting bosons in the flux ladder—the system that has been recently realized by means of ultracold atoms in the specially designed optical lattice [M. Atala, M. Aidelsburger, M. Lohse, J. T. Barreiro, B. Paredes, and I. Bloch, Nat. Phys. 10, 588 (2014)1745-247310.1038/nphys2998]. It is argued that, for the system parameters corresponding to two degenerate minima in the Bloch dispersion relation, the ground state is a fragmented condensate. We study the Bogoliubov depletion of this condensate and discuss the role of boundary conditions.</subfield>
      <subfield code="9">APS</subfield>
    </datafield>
